The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, July 2: Planning Commission deputy chairman Montek Singh Ahluwalia today said economic growth might moderate to about 7.9-8 per cent in the current fiscal, while adding that inflation would not affect expansion in the medium and long term.                             
	 New Delhi, July 2: The government today said the five year-period for export oriented units (EOUs) to earn net foreign exchange might be extended if they were unable to export because of bans on shipments.                             
	 New York, July 2: The Ruias-promoted Essar group has got close to Rs 200 crore for withdrawing its bid for the US steel firm Esmark. The payment will be made by Esmarks successful suitor  the Russian firm Severstal.                            
	 Madrid, July 2: Venezuelan national oil firm PDVSA is keen on taking a stake in Indian Oil Corporations (IOC) Rs 29,777-crore Paradip refinery in exchange for committing itself to almost half of the crude oil needed for processing in the 15 million tonnes-a- year refinery.                            
	 New Delhi, July 2: Coal India Limited (CIL) plans to develop seven underground mines with foreign technology on a turnkey basis and phase out 60 loss-making manual mines that have become unfit for mining.                                                                                                                         
